issue.title: Can't get logging to work
issue.body:
I am just getting started with pyscript. I have it running, but logging doesn't seem to work.

in my `configuration.yaml` I have
```yaml
logger:
  default: info
  logs:
    custom_components.pyscript: debug
```

My script file is this
```python
@service
def hello(name: str = "world"):
    log.debug(f"[HELLO] entered hello(name={name!r})")

    light.toggle(entity_id="light.shelly_dimmer_master_sitting_room")

    msg = f"Hello, {name}!"
    log.info(f"[HELLO] {msg}")
    task.sleep(0.1)  # example of yielding; keeps HA responsive
    log.debug("[HELLO] leaving hello()")
```

I can run the script, and it toggles the light. This tells me the script can run and it works.

However, Going to Settings -> System -> Logs and looking at the `Home Assistant Core` log, I don't see any of my log messages. Logs from other things in my system are there, but nothing from my hello.py script. 

Any help would be appreciated. 

P.S. I've restarted HASS a few times, so that's not the problem.

comment.body:
Ah, figured it out.

The logs are written to `config/home-assistant.log` but they were **not** show up in the UI at Settings -> System -> Logs -> Home Assistant Core. That's because they were `INFO` and `DEBUG` logs which seem to be filtered out in the UI. `WARNING` logs show up from my script in the UI.

While using CurrencyPP with Flow Launcher 1.20.2, I ran into a crash caused by a SyntaxWarning in Python.

Error message:
Flow Launcher version: 1.20.2
OS Version: 26100.4946
Python Path: C:\Users\AlifPC\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python313\pythonw.exe

CurrencyPP Exception:
C:\Users\AlifPC\AppData\Roaming\FlowLauncher\Plugins\CurrencyPP-4.0.0\src\exchange.py:164:
SyntaxWarning: invalid escape sequence '\d'
elif re.search('\d', validated):

Cause:
In Python 3.12+ '\d' is treated as an invalid escape sequence.
The regex line should use a raw string instead.

Current:
elif re.search('\d', validated):

Fix:
elif re.search(r'\d', validated):

Steps to reproduce:

Install CurrencyPP 4.0.0 on Flow Launcher 1.20.2

Run a currency query

Plugin crashes with the above exception

Environment:

Flow Launcher: 1.20.2

CurrencyPP: 4.0.0

OS: Windows 11 (Build 26100.4946)

Python: 3.13 (x64)

Log:
I‚Äôve uploaded the log file here:
[2025-08-17.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21818144/2025-08-17.txt)

Most lemmas about these do not require the enorm to be positive definite (i.e., work fine if a nontrivial element has zero enorm), or can be rephrased easily. A handful of lemmas do require this condition.

fix: allow build steps to access timezone (#28510)

## Problem

The deprecated attribute linter was failing with timezone database errors:
```
unable to locate share/zoneinfo in the local timezone database at /etc/localtime
```

This was happening because the linter uses `Std.Time.PlainDate.now` to compare dates, which requires timezone information.

## Solution

Add `-ro /etc/timezone` to `landrun` shell options.

## Changes

- Add timezone permissions to `shell` in `.github/build.in.yml`
- Regenerated all build workflow files (`build.yml`, `bors.yml`, `build_fork.yml`)

This should fix the deprecated attribute linter failures in CI.
